<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-12-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="263" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                    <head>No. 976.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Curry</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-12-08"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 8,
                            1887</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>The Department of State informs Mr. Curry that it has been advised by the
                        Spanish minister at Washington that the Spanish minister of foreign affairs
                        is willing to extend until Jane 30, 1888, the commercial agreement now in
                        force. Mr. Curry is therefore instructed to sign a protocol, as before,
                        extending the agreement.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>